Design a streaming CDC pipeline that captures changes from a multi-tenant PostgreSQL database using Debezium's Kafka Connect connector (reading PostgreSQL's logical decoding WAL via pgoutput), publishes change events to Cloud Pub/Sub with at-least-once delivery semantics, and ingests into BigQuery tenant-isolated datasets via Dataflow with Apache Beam. Implement real-time schema drift detection using add-only evolution policies (new nullable columns only) and controlled type promotions (SMALLINT→INT→BIGINT→NUMERIC for numerics, TEXT→VARCHAR when length-bounded), with rollback via versioned schemas in Schema Registry and Dead Letter Queues for failed records. Track lineage through Dataplex/Data Catalog. Validate data contracts with tenants through Avro schema enforcement, BigQuery authorized views, and PACT-based contract testing.

## Dataflow Pipeline Implementation

```java
public class CdcToBigQueryPipeline {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        PipelineOptions options = PipelineOptionsFactory.fromArgs(args).create();
        Pipeline pipeline = Pipeline.create(options);

        pipeline
            .apply("ReadFromPubSub", PubsubIO.readStrings()
                .withSubscription("projects/project/subscriptions/cdc-sub"))
            .apply("ParseAndValidate", ParDo.of(new CdcMessageParser()))
            .apply("DetectSchemaDrift", ParDo.of(new SchemaDriftDetector()))
            .apply("RouteByTenant", WithKeys.of(msg -> msg.getTenantId()))
            .apply(GroupByKey.create())
            .apply("WriteToBigQuery", ParDo.of(new BigQueryTenantWriter()));
    }
}

public class SchemaDriftDetector extends DoFn<CdcMessage, CdcMessage> {
    private static final double NULLITY_THRESHOLD = 0.15;
    private static final double TYPE_CHANGE_THRESHOLD = 0.05;

    @ProcessElement
    public void process(@Element String raw, OutputReceiver<CdcMessage> out) {
        JsonNode record = new ObjectMapper().readTree(raw);
        Struct schema = extractSchema(record);

        Map<String, DriftMetric> currentMetrics = computeMetrics(record);
        SchemaEvolution evolution = detectEvolution(schema, currentMetrics);

        if (evolution.hasBreakingChange()) {
            sendToDeadLetterQueue(raw, evolution.getViolations());
            return;
        }

        if (evolution.hasSafeDrift()) {
            emitSchemaMigrationEvent(evolution);
        }

        out.output(new CdcMessage(record, evolution.getAppliedSchema()));
    }

    private SchemaEvolution detectEvolution(Struct schema, Map<String, DriftMetric> metrics) {
        SchemaEvolution.Builder evolution = SchemaEvolution.builder();

        for (Map.Entry<String, DriftMetric> entry : metrics.entrySet()) {
            String col = entry.getKey();
            DriftMetric m = entry.getValue();

            if (!schema.hasColumn(col)) {
                evolution.addColumn(ColumnEvolution.newColumn(col, m.getType(), m.isNullable()));
            } else if (m.getNullityPercent() > NULLITY_THRESHOLD && !schema.isNullable(col)) {
                evolution.promoteToNullable(col);
            } else if (isSafeTypePromotion(schema.getType(col), m.getInferredType())) {
                evolution.promoteType(col, m.getInferredType());
            }
        }
        return evolution.build();
    }
}
```

## Drift Detection Thresholds

| Metric | Threshold | Action |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| Column nullity % | >15% over 10min window | Flag for nullable promotion |
| Type mismatch rate | >5% records incompatible | Block and alert; require manual review |
| New column detection | First occurrence | Auto-add if nullable, else DLQ |
| Schema evolution lag | >30s between versions | Pause pipeline, alert ops |
| Backward incompatible change | Any detected | Immediate DLQ, rollback schema version |

## Rollback Strategy

