## Pipeline Architecture

**Ingestion Layer (Pub/Sub)**
- Publish 50 GB/day of JSON clickstream events to a single regional Pub/Sub topic
- Enable schema validation on the subscription to reject malformed messages early
- Configure 7-day message retention to enable reprocessing if needed

**Dataflow Pipeline (Apache Beam)**

```javascript
// 1) Subscribe to Pub/Sub and parse JSON
const rawMessages = p
  .apply('ReadFromPubSub', PubsubIO.readStrings()
    .fromTopic('projects/my-project/topics/clickstream-events'))
  .apply('ParseJSON', ParDo.of(new ParseJSONFn()));

// 2) Per-field validation with PII masking
const validated = rawMessages
  .apply('ValidateAndMask', ParDo.of(new ValidateAndMaskPIIFn()));

// 3) Route invalids to errors table
validated.invalidRecords
  .apply('WriteToErrors', BigQueryIO.write()
    .to('my-project:clickstream.errors')
    .withFailedInsertHook(errorHandler));

// 4) Write valid records to partitioned BigQuery table
validated.validRecords
  .apply('WriteToBigQuery', BigQueryIO.write()
    .to('my-project:clickstream.events')
    .withSchema(eventSchema)
    .withCreateDisposition(CreateDisposition.CREATE_IF_NEEDED)
    .withWriteDisposition(WriteDisposition.WRITE_APPEND));
```

**BigQuery Tables**
- `events`: Partitioned by `_PARTITIONTIME`, clustered by `tenant_id` and `event_type`
- `errors`: Partitioned by ingestion timestamp; stores rejected records with error reasons
- `event_heatmap`: Partitioned by window timestamp; stores rolling 24h aggregates

**Rolling 24h Heatmap (Sliding Window)**

```javascript
// Aggregate per-tenant event_type frequencies using a sliding window
const heatmap = validated.validRecords
  .apply('SlidingWindow24h', Window.into(SlidingWindows.of(Duration.standardHours(24))
    .every(Duration.standardHours(1))))
  .apply('GroupByTenantAndType', GroupByKey.create(['tenant_id', 'event_type']))
  .apply('CountEvents', ParDo.of(new CountEventsFn()))
  .apply('WriteHeatmapTable', BigQueryIO.write()
    .to('my-project:clickstream.event_heatmap')
    .withSchema(heatmapSchema)
    .withCreateDisposition(CreateDisposition.CREATE_IF_NEEDED));
```

## Validation and PII Masking Strategy

```javascript
class ValidateAndMaskPIIFn extends DoFn {
  processElement = (element, ctx) => {
    const errors = [];
    const masked = { ...element };

    // Validate required fields
    if (!element.tenant_id) errors.push('missing tenant_id');
    if (!element.event_type) errors.push('missing event_type');
    if (!element.timestamp) errors.push('missing timestamp');

    // Validate data types
    if (typeof element.timestamp !== 'string') errors.push('invalid timestamp format');

    // Mask PII fields
    if (element.user_email) masked.user_email = maskEmail(element.user_email);
    if (element.ip_address) masked.ip_address = maskIP(element.ip_address);

    if (errors.length > 0) {
      ctx.output('invalid', { ...masked, _error_reason: errors.join('; ') });
    } else {
      ctx.output('valid', masked);
    }
  };
}
```

## Testing Strategy

| Test Type | Approach |
|-----------|----------|
| **Unit Tests** | Validate `ValidateAndMaskPIIFn` with valid and invalid payloads, including edge cases (empty strings, nulls, malformed JSON) |
| **Integration Tests** | Synthesize 10,000 messages with controlled tenant and event distributions; verify BigQuery counts match expected values |
| **Load Tests** | Publish at 2x expected rate (~1.2 MB/sec) to verify Dataflow autoscaling and BigQuery streaming insert limits |
| **Chaos Tests** | Terminate Dataflow workers mid-stream; verify dead-letter queue catches messages and reprocessing succeeds |

## Rollback Plan

| Scenario | Action |
|----------|--------|
| Bad code deploy | Dataflow supports rollback via pipeline version; redeploy the previous template |
| Schema mismatch | Pause Pub/Sub subscription, fix schema, replay from snapshot |
| BigQuery quota exceeded | Enable exponential backoff retry; alert at >80% quota utilization |
| Data corruption | Truncate affected partition via DML; replay from Pub/Sub within the 7-day retention window |

**Recovery Command:**
```bash
# Pause pipeline and replay from timestamp
dataflow stop --job_id=JOB_ID && \
pubsub snapshots create my-snapshot --subscription=clickstream-sub && \
pubsub seek my-snapshot --subscription=clickstream-sub --time=2024-01-01T00:00:00Z
```

Approach: a Dataflow streaming pipeline reading tenant-scoped JSON from Pub/Sub, consulting per-tenant schemas from a registry stored in Cloud Storage and cataloged in Data Catalog, and mapping to a shared BigQuery schema with backward-compatible field handling.

**Schema Registry Design**
- Store Avro/Protobuf schemas per tenant in Cloud Storage buckets organized as `gs://tenant-schemas/{tenant_id}/schemas/{version}.avsc`
- Register schemas in Data Catalog with tenant tags, PII sensitivity labels, and lineage metadata
- Maintain a schema version manifest in Cloud Spanner for fast tenant-scoped lookups

**Versioning & Compatibility Checks**
- Use semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) where MAJOR changes break backward compatibility
- Before deployment, run Avro schema resolution: new schema must pass forward-compatibility test against latest approved schema (consumer tests with old producer data)
- Store compatibility matrix in Cloud Storage: `gs://tenant-schemas/{tenant_id}/compatibility/matrix.json`
- Data Catalog entry includes last validated version and approval timestamp

**Dynamic Adaptation & Migration Triggers**
- Dataflow job polls schema manifest every 60 seconds; on new version, emits metric and continues processing existing fields while buffering new fields to a raw JSON column
- SideInput pattern provides per-window schema cache: `PCollectionView<Map<String, String>> tenantSchemas`
- Migration trigger: Cloud Function on Storage object create → validates compatibility → updates Spanner manifest → sends Pub/Sub notification to Dataflow to refresh side input
- Backward compatibility preserved by treating unknown fields as nullable or routing to `_raw_payload` JSON column in BigQuery

**Testing with Evolving Schemas**
- Unit tests: JUnit parameterized tests over schema version tuples (v1→v2, v1→v3, v2→v3) using Helix TestKit schema diff generator
- Integration tests: TestPubSub emulator + LocalTemplateOverride to simulate schema version jumps mid-pipeline
- Chaos testing: BigQuery loader with schema assertion using Google Cloud Test Lab to verify no data loss across 1000 schema mutations
- Contract tests: Define expected TableRow outputs in JSON; Dataflow assertJ verifies field presence, nullability, and type coercion

**Audit Trail for Field-Level Changes**
- Cloud Logging entries per schema change: `{tenant_id, field_name, old_type, new_type, changed_by, timestamp, compatibility_result}`
- Data Catalog audit log integration exports to BigQuery audit dataset for compliance queries
- Cloud Audit Logs (Admin Activity) captures who approved schema changes with approval justification field
- BigQuery INFORMATION_SCHEMA.JOURNAL Entries track schema evolution per table
- Field-level lineage via Dataflow metrics: `schema_field_added_count`, `schema_field_deprecated_count` per tenant per day

```java
public class TenantSchemaMapper extends DoFn<String, TableRow> {
  private transient Map<String, Schema> tenantSchemas;

  @Setup
  public void setup() {
    tenantSchemas = loadSchemasFromSideInput();
  }

  @ProcessElement
  public void process(@Element String json, @TenantId String tenantId, 
                      OutputReceiver<TableRow> out, ProcessContext c) {
    Schema schema = tenantSchemas.get(tenantId);
    GenericRecord record = new GenericData.Record(schema);
    JsonNode node = new ObjectMapper().readTree(json);

    for (Schema.Field field : schema.getFields()) {
      if (node.has(field.name())) {
        record.put(field.name(), node.get(field.name()).asText());
      } else {
        record.put(field.name(), null); // backward compatible
      }
    }

    // Buffer unknown fields to raw column
    out.output(convertToTableRow(record, node));
  }
}
```

